        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Types</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Though Alfa Laval manufactures a few different centrifuges, the most common models are the disc stack centrifuge and the decanter centrifuge.
        </p>

        <!-- Disc Stack -->
        <div id="disc-stack-centrifuge">
          <div class="md:flex md:gap-6 items-start mb-4">
            <div class="md:w-1/2 mb-4 md:mb-0">
              <img
                src="/images/alfa-laval-centrifuge/alfa-laval-disc-centrifuge-bowl-cross-section-400-1.jpg"
                alt="Alfa Laval Disc Stack Centrifuge Bowl Cross Section showing disc stack and sludge ports"
                width="400" height="222"
                loading="lazy"
                class="rounded-lg w-full"
              />
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1 text-center">Alfa Laval Disc Stack Centrifuge Bowl Section</p>
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-navy mb-3">Disc Stack Centrifuge</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                A disc stack centrifuge is an industrial centrifuge that can separate small sediment and immiscible liquid contaminants from a base liquid. The main feature of Alfa Laval disc stack centrifuges is the high centrifugal force of <strong>up to 10,000 Gs with a bowl RPM of over 12,000</strong>.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-3">
                Another important aspect of a disc stack centrifuge is its ability to separate two insoluble fluids from each other while also separating the solids.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-4">
            <div id="manual-clean" class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Manual Clean</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                A disc stack centrifuge is available in two configurations. The simple version separates and retains the solids within the bowl for manual extrication. This centrifuge is suitable for liquid-liquid separation with minimal solids (&lt; 0.05%) and is known as a manual clean centrifuge.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="self-clean" class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Self Clean</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                A self-cleaning disc stack centrifuge separates the base fluid from another insoluble fluid while also separating the solids. The design of this centrifuge allows it to self-eject the separated solids automatically while the bowl is still rotating. This centrifuge does not require manual cleaning of the solids.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Decanter -->
        <div id="decanter-centrifuge" class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-gray-100">
          <div class="md:flex md:gap-6 items-start">
            <div class="md:w-1/2 mb-4 md:mb-0">
              <img
                src="/images/alfa-laval-centrifuge/Decanter-Cross-Section-600.jpg"
