        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
            <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What types of Alfa Laval centrifuges does Dolphin Centrifuge supply?</summary>
            <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Dolphin Centrifuge supplies Alfa Laval disc stack centrifuges (MOPX, WHPX, MAPX, MAB, WSB series) and Alfa Laval decanter centrifuges (NX-314, NX-418, NX-428) as complete system modules. The Dolphin DMPX and DMB series are purpose-built centrifuge modules using Alfa Laval centrifuge bowls as the core separation component.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
            <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What is the difference between an Alfa Laval disc stack and decanter centrifuge?</summary>
            <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Alfa Laval disc stack centrifuges (MOPX, MAPX, WHPX series) operate at 7,000+ Gs and excel at liquid-liquid separation (oil/water) with fine particle removal down to 0.5 microns. They are used for diesel, lube oil, and coolant purification. Alfa Laval decanter centrifuges (NX series) operate at 3,000+ Gs and handle high-solids sludge dewatering, drilling mud processing, and crude oil tank bottom recovery.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
            <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">How much does an Alfa Laval centrifuge cost?</summary>
            <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Alfa Laval centrifuge pricing varies widely by model. A remanufactured small disc stack centrifuge (DMB-028 equivalent) starts around $15,000–$30,000. A new Dolphin DMPX-028 complete system module runs $35,000–$55,000. Larger models (DMPX-070) and decanter systems range from $75,000–$200,000+. Contact Dolphin Centrifuge at <a href="tel:+12485222573" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold">(248) 522-2573</a> for current pricing.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
            <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What industries use Alfa Laval centrifuges?</summary>
            <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Alfa Laval centrifuges are used in marine (fuel and lube oil purification), power generation (turbine lube oil), oil and gas (crude oil dehydration, diesel polishing), food and beverage (edible oil, dairy, beer/wine), pharmaceutical (cell separation, broth clarification), wastewater treatment, and industrial manufacturing (coolant recovery, metalworking fluids).</p>
          </details>
          <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
            <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Does Dolphin Centrifuge supply used Alfa Laval centrifuges?</summary>
            <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Yes. Dolphin Centrifuge rebuilds and remanufactures used Alfa Laval centrifuges to like-new condition, replacing all wear components, gaskets, and bearings. Remanufactured units are tested before shipment and include a warranty. This is a cost-effective alternative to new equipment — typically 40–60% of new cost. Contact <a href="tel:+12485222573" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold">(248) 522-2573</a> for current inventory.</p>
          </details>
